*As the* Planning Poker Development Team
*I want* to create a new planning poker room and receive a unique shareable link
*So that* I can invite participants to join the session

*Acceptance Criteria*
- AC01: Visiting the app with no room parameter automatically generates a unique room ID and updates the browser URL to include it as a query parameter
- AC02: The generated room ID conforms to the backend slug format (lowercase alphanumeric segments separated by dashes)
- AC03: The URL displayed in the browser address bar after redirect is the shareable room link
- AC04: Each fresh visit to the root URL generates a different room ID

*Out of Scope*
- Entering a display name or joining the room as a named participant (separate story)
- Joining a room via a shared link (separate story)
- A landing page or explicit "Create room" button

*Technical Notes*
- Generate a random slug client-side that conforms to the backend room ID regex (`^[a-z0-9]{4,32}(-[a-z0-9]{4,32})*$`)
- Update the browser URL to `/?room=<id>` using client-side routing without a full page reload
- Initiate a WebSocket connection to the backend with the generated room ID — the first connection to a room is assigned host status by the backend
- Backend WebSocket endpoint: `wss://planning-poker-backend-ymq7.onrender.com/ws?room=<roomId>&name=<displayName>`

*Testing Notes*
- Verify that visiting the root URL with no `?room=` parameter redirects the browser to `/?room=<generated-id>`
- Verify the generated room ID matches the expected slug format
- Verify that two separate fresh visits to the root URL produce different room IDs
- Verify a WebSocket connection is attempted to the backend with the generated room ID
